One Lekan Olumodi was on Tuesday arraigned before a Chief Magistrates’ Court, sitting in Ado Ekiti for allegedly stealing electricity generating set and beer after breaking into the shop. Oloumodi, 27, who is standing trial on the two-count charge, was accused of stealing a generating set and two different cartons of beer. The defendant of no fixed address, according to the police prosecutor, Sgt Olubu Apata committed the offences on February 19, at about 3:30 am. at Olorunda Community in Ado-Ekiti. Apata alleged that the defendant broke into a shop, belonging to one Adamolekun Abosede, and carted away electricity generating set valued at N35,000, bottles of alcoholic beverages, estimated at N20,000 and a carton each of Trophy and Goldberg beer. The offences, he said contravened Section 413 (i) and 390 (9) of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ekiti State, 2020. The defendant however, pleaded not guilty to the charges, while the prosecutor asked the court for adjournment to enable him study the case file and present his witnesses. Mr Timi Omotosho who is counsel to the defendant prayed the court to grant his client bail, promising that he would not jump bail. Magistrate Kehinde Awosika, granted bail to the defendant in the sum of N50,000, with one surety in like sum and subsequently adjourned the case until April 6, 2020 for hearing. 